<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1445,1974]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,324,1522,1548]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Remarks:</emphasis>
The detailed description of the life cycle and development of 
<taxonomicName box="[1091,1381,1523,1548]" class="Arachnida" family="Hydrodromidae" genus="Hydrodroma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="despiciens">
<emphasis box="[1091,1381,1523,1548]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Hydrodroma despiciens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was published by 
<bibRefCitation author="Meyer" box="[320,492,1561,1587]" pageId="1" pageNumber="32" refString="Meyer, E. (1985) Der Entwicklungszyklus von Hydrodroma despiciens (O. F. Muller 1776) (Acari. Hydrodromidae). Archiv fur Hydrobiologie, Supplement 66, 3, 321 - 453." type="journal article" year="1985">
Meyer (
<number box="[418,483,1561,1587]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="1985.0">1985</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
immediately before 
<bibRefCitation author="Wiles" box="[752,914,1561,1587]" pageId="1" pageNumber="34" refString="Wiles, P. R. (1985) The systematics of the British Hydrodromidae Viets, 1936. Archiv fur Hydrobiologie, Supplement 70 (3), 365 - 403." type="journal article" year="1985">
Wiles (
<number box="[841,906,1561,1587]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="1985.0">1985</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
cleared up the taxonomic situation of the European (sub)species of the genus. In a later paper, 
<bibRefCitation author="Meyer" box="[771,933,1600,1626]" pageId="1" pageNumber="32" refString="Meyer, E. (1989) Comparative studies on the biology of water mites of the genus Hydrodroma (Actinedida: Hydrodromidae). In: Channabasawanna, G. P. &amp; Viraktamath, C. A. (eds.), Progress in Acarology Vol 1. Oxford and IBH Publ. Co, New Dehli, pp. 433 - 440." type="journal article" year="1989">
Meyer (
<number box="[863,924,1600,1626]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="1989.0">1989</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
indicated that the population on which her study was based, represented 
<taxonomicName box="[504,865,1639,1664]" class="Arachnida" family="Hydrodromidae" genus="Hydrodroma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="despiciens" subSpecies="pilosa">
<emphasis box="[504,865,1639,1664]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Hydrodroma despiciens pilosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, a subspecies raised to species rank by 
<bibRefCitation author="Gerecke" pageId="1" pageNumber="31" refString="Gerecke, R. (1991) Taxonomische, faunistische und okologische Untersuchungen an Wassermilben aus Sizilien unter Berucksichtigung anderer aquatischer Invertebraten. Lauterbornia, 7, 1 - 304." type="journal article" year="1991">
Gerecke (
<number box="[160,224,1677,1703]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="1991.0">1991</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
. A revision of both slide material from Meyer's PhD thesis and newly collected populations confirms that exclusively 
<taxonomicName box="[350,586,1716,1741]" class="Arachnida" family="Hydrodromidae" genus="Hydrodroma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pilosa">
<emphasis box="[350,586,1716,1741]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Hydrodroma pilosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was, and still is, present in the Mindelsee. In the course of this study, further characters were detected that separate 
<taxonomicName box="[699,809,1755,1780]" class="Arachnida" family="Hydrodromidae" genus="Hydrodroma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pilosa">
<emphasis box="[699,809,1755,1780]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">H. pilosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<taxonomicName box="[882,1042,1755,1780]" class="Arachnida" family="Hydrodromidae" genus="Hydrodroma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="despiciens">
<emphasis box="[882,1042,1755,1780]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">H. despiciens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: Integument papillae are sharply pointed (in 
<taxonomicName box="[287,446,1793,1818]" class="Arachnida" family="Hydrodromidae" genus="Hydrodroma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="despiciens">
<emphasis box="[287,446,1793,1818]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">H. despiciens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
apically rounded) and more acetabula 
<number box="[905,943,1793,1819]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="7.0" valueMax="8.0" valueMin="6.0">6-8</number>
(in 
<taxonomicName box="[992,1150,1793,1818]" class="Arachnida" family="Hydrodromidae" genus="Hydrodroma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="despiciens">
<emphasis box="[992,1150,1793,1818]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">H. despiciens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<number box="[1158,1198,1793,1819]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="5.0" valueMax="6.0" valueMin="4.0">4-6</number>
) lie in parallel rows where the genital flaps have their maximum width. These differences show that the two taxa should be considered separate species. Information so far published on the biology of 
<taxonomicName box="[1043,1322,1871,1896]" class="Arachnida" family="Hydrodromidae" genus="Hydrodroma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="despiciens">
<emphasis box="[1043,1322,1871,1896]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Hydrodroma despiciens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, might in reality refer to 
<taxonomicName box="[325,432,1909,1934]" class="Arachnida" family="Hydrodromidae" genus="Hydrodroma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pilosa">
<emphasis box="[325,432,1909,1934]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">H. pilosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, or cannot be interpreted with certainty. Consequently, with regard to its life cycle, 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Hydrodromidae" genus="Hydrodroma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="despiciens">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">H. despiciens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is still a mostly unknown species.
</paragraph>
